articles.description: James Scott and Nick Masterson each scored 27 points, Anthony Wilson calmly sank two free throws on his first trip to the line with 1.1 seconds on the clock and Kennesaw State defeated Florida Gulf Coast 97-93 Thursday night, ending the Eagles'...
articles.headline: Kennesaw State beats FGCU 97-93, ending 13-game win streak

articles.description: Shaquille Morris had 23 points and 13 rebounds, including a tie-breaking putback in the final two minutes, to help No. 19 Wichita State defeat Temple 93-86 on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Morris leads No. 19 Wichita State past Temple 93-86

images.caption: Zach Brown misses the triple, but Shaquille Morris is there to clean up for the lay-in and the foul.
images.name: Morris' and-1 bucket gives the Shockers the lead

articles.description: Corey Davis Jr. and Devin Davis each scored 16 points, and Houston beat No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62 on Thursday night to snap the nation's longest winning streak at 16 games.
articles.headline: Houston ends No. 5 Cincinnati's 16-game win streak, 67-62

images.caption: The student section celebrates Houston's first win over an AP top-5 team since 1996.
images.name: Houston' student section storms the court after W

articles.description: Cam Ward scored 14 points and Drew Urquhart and Everett Duncan added 13 each as Vermont defeated New Hampshire 71-58 on Thursday night for the Catamounts' 15th consecutive victory.
articles.headline: Vermont beats UNH 71-58 for 15th straight victory

articles.description: Vasa Pusica scored 17 of his 24 points in the first half and Anthony Green tied a career-high with 16 points as Northeastern held off Drexel 75-69 on Thursday night for its fourth straight win.
articles.headline: Pusica's big first half helps Huskies hold off Dragons

articles.description: Garrison Mathews had 17 points as Lipscomb got hot in the second half to beat Stetson 82-73 to win its third straight in Atlantic Sun Conference play on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Lipscomb gets hot in 2nd half, beats Stetson 82-73

videos.description: Sagaba Konate denies PJ Washington at the rim leading to a Jevon Carter 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Konate block leads to Carter 3

videos.description: WVU's Sagaba Konate forces a missed dunk on defense and then throws it down with two hands on the other end.
videos.headline: Konate rocks rim early

videos.description: Kevin Knox keeps Kentucky close early with back-to-back dunks.
videos.headline: Knox jams back-to-back dunks

videos.description: Sagaba Konate gets another block, this time on Kevin Knox against the backboard.
videos.headline: Konate pins one against the boards

videos.description: Sagaba Konate denies Jarred Vanderbilt setting up Jevon Carter for the fastbreak layup.
videos.headline: Konate blocks, Carter scores

videos.description: Hamidou Diallo knocks down an open 3-pointer to make it a 7-point game for the Wildcats.
videos.headline: Diallo cuts into WVU's lead with 3

videos.description: Kevin Knox is left all alone for a 3-pointer to make it 56-50 as the Wildcats close the gap.
videos.headline: Knox makes it a 6-point game with 3

videos.description: Kentucky takes a 58-56 lead with a fast-break hammer from Kevin Knox.
videos.headline: Knox gives UK lead with fast-break dunk

videos.description: James Bolden gets the Mountaineers back in front with back-to-back 3-pointers.
videos.headline: Bolden hits back-to-back 3's for WVU

videos.description: James Bolden knocks down a 3-pointer to tie it at 74.
videos.headline: Bolden ties it with 3 for WVU

videos.description: Kevin Knox knocks down his fifth 3-pointer to put the Wildcats back in front 77-74.
videos.headline: Knox answers with a 3 for WVU

videos.description: Nick Richards gets the putback dunk uncontested at the rim to put Kentucky up 5 late against WVU.
videos.headline: Richards gets the putback dunk for UK

videos.description: Kevin Knox scores 34 points to fuel the Wildcats to an 83-76 victory on the road against the No. 7 Mountaineers.
videos.headline: Kentucky takes down No. 7 West Virginia

videos.description: Kentucky freshman Kevin Knox says his team just kept fighting in their second half comeback against the Mountaineers and that people counted them out facing the number 7 team in the country.
videos.headline: Knox: 'We gotta prove people wrong'

videos.description: The Wildcats, behind Kevin Knox's career-high 34 points, pull off a huge comeback on the road to win their first game against a ranked opponent.
videos.headline: UK storms back from 17 down, stuns No. 7 WVU 83-76
